# Security Policy

## Project Scope

This project is a **local password generator and vault learning application** built with HTML, CSS and JavaScript.

It is designed for:

- educational purposes  
- portfolio demonstration  
- practicing frontend logic and browser storage  
- learning basic security awareness  

⚠️ This application is **NOT intended for real-world password storage**.

Passwords are stored in **LocalStorage without encryption** and can be accessed by anyone using the same browser profile.

---

## Supported Versions

There are currently no versioned releases.

The **latest version in the main branch** is considered the only supported version.

Older forks or downloaded copies may contain outdated or insecure logic.

---

## Known Security Limitations

This project intentionally does **not implement production-level security features**, such as:

- encryption of stored data  
- authentication or user accounts  
- secure password hashing  
- backend storage or secure APIs  
- protection against XSS via browser extensions  
- device-level access protection  

These limitations are part of the learning scope of this project.

---

## Reporting a Vulnerability

If you discover a vulnerability or security concern, please report it by opening a **GitHub Issue**.

Please include:

- a clear description of the issue  
- steps to reproduce  
- expected vs actual behaviour  
- affected file or feature  
- browser and device information  
- screenshots or code snippets if relevant  

---

## Responsible Disclosure

Please **do not publicly disclose security issues** before they are reviewed.

This helps prevent misuse and allows time to improve the project.

---

## Future Security Improvements (Planned Learning Goals)

This project may evolve with future features such as:

- encrypted vault storage  
- master password protection  
- session locking  
- password strength analytics  
- export/import with secure formats  
- backend integration  
- authentication systems  
- secure random generation improvements  

These features are part of the long-term development learning roadmap.

---

Thank you for helping improve this project.
